author: @theMiaow
text: Precision -> it focuses more on the quality aspect in how the model actually predicted true positives in a significant amount. Thus, higher precision results in lower false positive rates.  Recall -> it focuses more on the quantity of positive INSTANCES (both false and true positives are included) that were identified by the model. Thus, higher recall results in lower false negative rates.
